<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="503" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal coloration from yellow to dark brown or black, scattered white spots sometimes present; marginal band white intersected by greyish black transversal stripes; marginal line gold yellow to orange. Prostatic and seminal vesicle small in relation to the penis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
This species was included in the 
<emphasis box="[826,931,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">P. bi col or</emphasis>
complex due to its coloration pattern. Some specimens reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[440,508,367,392]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">Brazil</collectingCountry>
as 
<emphasis box="[548,653,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">P. b i c o l o r</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bahia" box="[673,920,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" refString="Bahia, J. &amp; Padula, V. (2009) First record of Pseudoceros bicolor and Pericelis cata (Platyhelminthes: Polycladida) from Brazil. Marine Biodiversity Records, 2, 1 - 5. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / s 1755267209000918" type="journal article" year="2009">
Bahia &amp; Padula 
<number box="[862,920,368,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) were in fact 
<taxonomicName box="[1079,1246,367,392]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="rawlinsonae">
<emphasis box="[1079,1246,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">P. rawlinsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This was found out after the review of the 
<emphasis box="[460,567,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">P. bi col or</emphasis>
complex (
<bibRefCitation author="Litvaitis" box="[692,924,404,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" refString="Litvaitis, M. K., Bolanos, D. M. &amp; Quiroga, S. Y. (2010) When names are wrong and colours deceive: unraveling the Pseudoceros bicolor species complex (Turbellaria: Polycladida). Journal of Natural History, 44, 829 - 845. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930903537074" type="journal article" year="2010">
Litvaitis 
<emphasis box="[796,847,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[864,924,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="2010.0">2010</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), which has clearly delimited the differences between these two species and made an emendation to the species description. It was observed that differences in marginal lines (
<emphasis box="[328,433,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">P. b i c o l o r</emphasis>
, bright yellow to greenish or absent, and 
<taxonomicName box="[908,1075,476,501]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="rawlinsonae">
<emphasis box="[908,1075,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">P. rawlinsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, golden yellow to orange) were reflected in the species separation genetically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
It is suggested that specimens collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[671,739,548,573]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">Brazil</collectingCountry>
should be included in a futher comparative molecular analysis between 
<emphasis box="[255,364,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">P. b i c o l o r</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[431,601,583,608]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="rawlinsonae">
<emphasis box="[431,601,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">P. rawlinsonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Our specimens are in accordance with characteristics presented in the original description and in the revision by Litivaitis 
<emphasis box="[756,814,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[832,894,620,644]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="2010.0">2010</number>
). We found both smaller and bigger specimens (variation between 
<number box="[368,382,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="8.0">8</number>
<date box="[390,426,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
x 
<quantity box="[412,426,655,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="6.0">6</quantity>
</date>
mm and 
<date box="[534,618,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="2011-10-19">
<number box="[534,562,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="19.0">19</number>
x 
<quantity box="[591,618,656,680]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="11.0">11</quantity>
</date>
mm) than originally described (
<date box="[983,1055,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="1917-10-07">
<number box="[983,1011,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="17.0">17</number>
x 
<quantity box="[1041,1055,656,679]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="7.0">7</quantity>
</date>
mm) by 
<bibRefCitation box="[1159,1401,655,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" refString="Bolanos, D. M., Quiroga, S. Y. &amp; Litvaitis, M. K. (2007) Five new species of cotylean flatworms (Platyhelminthes: Polycladida) from the wider Caribbean. Zootaxa, 1650, 1 - 23." type="journal article">
Bolaños 
<emphasis box="[1259,1308,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[1331,1393,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. In some specimens (
<figureCitation box="[354,424,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1726,1748]" captionTargetBox="[245,1345,508,1691]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[240,1352,501,1698]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Pseudoceros rawlinsonae (MNRJ-PLAT 01). A. in vivo; B. ventral view; C. detail of ventral view; D. detail from the anterior region, showing cerebral eyespots; E. detail from the anterior region showing tentacular eyespots; F. detail from the anterior ventral region; G. sagital section of the specimen body; H. sagittal section of male reproductive structures; I. sagittal section of female reproductive structures. ce: cerebral eyespots; cg: cement glands; cp: cement pouch; ep: epidermis; fg: female gonopore; it: main intestine; ma: male atrium; mg: male gonopore; ml: muscular layer; ph: pharynx; pt: pseudotentacles; pv: prostatic vesicle; ra: rhabdites; st: stylet; su: sucker; sv: seminal vesicle; te: tentacular eyespots; ut: uteri; va: vagina; vd: vas deferens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287267/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
Fig. 
<number box="[409,424,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="6.0">
<date box="[409,424,692,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">6</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
I), uteri were found to be full of eggs that reached 
<number box="[1018,1046,692,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="90.0">90</number>
µm diameter. The color variation found in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[399,467,727,752]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">Brazil</collectingCountry>
is illustrated in 
<figureCitation box="[648,716,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1743,1765]" captionTargetBox="[223,1360,794,1715]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[218,1370,789,1721]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Color variation in Pseudoceros rawlinsonae. A. MNRJ-PLAT 39; B. MNRJ-PLAT 37; C. MNRJ-PLAT 38; D. MNRJ-PLAT 01; E. MNRJ-PLAT 0 4." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/287268/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="503">
Fig. 
<number box="[699,716,728,751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="503" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
